titleproper.value: Guide to the Geoffrey T. Hellman Papers <lb/><date calendar="gregorian" era="ce">1842-1971</date><lb/> (Bulk<date calendar="gregorian" normal="1930/1970" era="ce" type="bulk"> 1930-1970)</date><lb/> <num>MSS.050</num>

author.value: Collection processed by Frank Walker, Jeanne Mixon, and Marilyn Petit.  Additional assistance: Marion Casey, Joan Grant, Russell James, William Koss, Robert Mcdermott, John-Paul Richiuso, and Pamela Smith.

creation.value: This finding aid was produced using ArchivesSpace <date>2017-06-16T20:43:12</date>

abstract.value: Geoffrey T. Hellman was a long-time contributor to <title ns2:type="simple" render="italic">The New Yorker</title> ("Talk of the Town" section in particular) and other periodicals, and wrote extensively about institutions such as: the American Museum of Natural History, the Smithsonian, and the Metropolitan Museum of Art. The collection gives a glimpse into the operation of <title ns2:type="simple" render="italic">The New Yorker</title> from the 1930's through 1960's. Research for Hellman's articles, his correspondence, and manuscripts are contained in this collection.

p.value: Materials are open to researchers. Please contact the Fales Library and Special Collections, fales.library@nyu.edu, 212-998-2596.

Published citations should take the following form:<lb/><lb/>Identification of item, date (if known); The Geoffrey T. Hellman Papers; MSS 050; box number; folder number; <address><addressline>Fales Library and Special Collections</addressline></address> , New York University Libraries.

<list><item> Hellman, Geoffrey T. "All about Geoffrey Hellman." <title type="simple" render="italic">Saturday Review of Literature</title>, v. XXX; no. 39; 1947.</item><item> The Geoffrey T. Hellman Papers; MSS 50; Fales Library and Special Collections, New York University Libraries.</item><item></item><item></item></list>

Series 16 consists of financial records documenting payments to Hellman for story ideas and articles published in <title type="simple" render="italic">The New Yorker</title>. Financial records of <title type="simple" render="italic">The New Yorker</title> payments to Hellman are also filed throughout the collection.
